{
  "text": "We also determined the effects of the overexpression of the isomerases on the detection of free thiols in F protein coexpressed with HN protein. We previously reported that levels of MPB binding to F protein were only slightly affected by coexpression with HN protein [CITATION_1] . Interestingly, the overexpression of ERdj5 or PDI protein resulted in the significantly decreased detection of free thiols in F protein in the presence of HN protein (Fig. 4B ). This result is consistent with the proposal that, due to the increased fusion in cells overexpressing the isomerases, more of the steady-state cell surface F protein is in a postfusion conformation, and that this conformation is not a substrate for thiol isomerases. No free thiols were detected in the HN protein (12), even when PDI or ERdj5 was over expressed (not shown).",
  "correct_citation": {
